HEADWORD: Blanket policy
<hw>Blanket policy</hw>
}</mhw>. <def>One that covers a group or class of things or properties
instead of one or more things mentioned individually, as where a
mortgage secures various debts as a group, or subjects a group or class
of different pieces of property to one general lien.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blanket stitch</ent>⟦br⟧
